<paragraph blockId="18.[830,1440,1263,1501]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">
AFFINITIES. According to the original description, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kovařík &amp; 1996" authorityYear="2004" baseAuthorityName="Lourenco &amp; Vachon" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[830,1060,1294,1317]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monodi">
<emphasis box="[830,1060,1294,1317]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">Orthochirus monodi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a hirsute fifth metasomal segment and a glabrous telson. This combination is otherwise present only in 
<taxonomicName authority="Kovařík &amp; 1996, 2004" authorityName="Kovařík &amp; 1996" authorityYear="2004" box="[1165,1336,1355,1378]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zagrosensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1165,1336,1355,1378]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">O. zagrosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1358,1432,1355,1378]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1358,1426,1355,1378]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">sp. n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
; however, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kovařík &amp; 1996" authorityYear="2004" baseAuthorityName="Lourenco &amp; Vachon" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[939,1056,1386,1409]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monodi">
<emphasis box="[939,1056,1386,1409]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">O. monodi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has hairs primarily on the ventral side of the fifth segment, whereas 
<taxonomicName authority="Kovařík &amp; 1996, 2004" authorityName="Kovařík &amp; 1996" authorityYear="2004" box="[1210,1369,1416,1439]" class="Arachnida" family="Buthidae" genus="Orthochirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Scorpiones" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zagrosensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1210,1369,1416,1439]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">O. zagrosensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1378,1440,1416,1439]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1378,1433,1416,1439]" pageId="18" pageNumber="17">sp. n</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
has them only on the dorsolateral surface and only in some specimens.
</paragraph>
